Für bitcoin Netzwerk
    Führe deploy.sh aus
    Prüfe mit check.sh
    Führe connect-nodes.sh aus, um Bitcoin Nodes im netzwerk hzzfg

    chmod +x *.sh
    ./deploy.sh
    ./check.sh
    ./connect-nodes.sh

    Cold-Wallet
        cold-key-A
            OS: NixOS minimal: AMD/intel
            Add to HA: off
            BIOS: OVMF
            machine q35
            SCSI: VirtI SCSI Single
            Qemu Agent: off
            Add EFI Disk: ON
            Pre-Enroll keys: opff
            TPM: off
            storage: qcow2
            grphic: none
            Bus/Device: SCSI 1
            storage local
            size: 10
            cache: none
            discard: ON
            Io Thread: ON
            SSD Emu: ON
            Read-Only: off
            Backup: off
            skip replication: ON
            Async IO: native
            sockets: 1
            Cores: 1
            CPU tyoe: Host
            Enable NUMA: off
            CPU-flags: default
            memory: 1024
            Reduktion der Netzwerk/Host interaktion
            ballooning: off
            allow KSM: off
            No network device: on
        cold-key-B
        cold-signer
            memory: 2048

NixOs Erstellung
    Ubuntu maschine SSH aktivieren
        sudo apt update
        sudo apt install -y openssh-server
        sudo systemctl enable ssh
        sudo systemctl start ssh